   "source": [
    "# Encryption\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = input(\"Enter Plain Text : \")\n",
    "input_key  = input(\"Enter Key        : \")\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = input_text.lower()\n",
    "input_key  = int(input_key)\n",
    "\n",
    "cipher_text = \"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "for character in input_text:\n",
    "  cipher_value  = ((ord(character)-ord('a')) + input_key) % 26\n",
    "  cipher_text  += chr(cipher_value + ord('a'))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Cipher Text      :\",cipher_text)"
   ]
  },

    "### Monoalphabetic Cipher"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "ywGCgc6QkdIg"
   },
   "source": [
    "The cipher line can be any permutation of the 26 characters which is mapped to the original sequence of 26 characters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 217,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "JXFvOBQpS_pj",
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdin",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Enter Plain Text :  hello\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Cipher Text      : itssg\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Encryption\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = input(\"Enter Plain Text : \")\n",
    "input_text = input_text.lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "cipher_text = \"\"\n",
    "cipher_line = \"qwertyuiopasdfghjklzxcvbnm\"\n",
    "\n",
    "for character in input_text:\n",
    "  index        = ord(character) - ord('a')\n",
    "  cipher_text += cipher_line[index]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Cipher Text      :\",cipher_text)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 218,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "UvZUDHBbqRoX",
    "outputId": "c8452f68-29b9-4253-9905-1cb0ac48c704",

     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Decryption\n",
    "\n",
    "plain_text = \"\"\n",
    "for character in cipher_text:\n",
    "  index = 0\n",
    "  for char in cipher_line:\n",
    "    if char == character:\n",
    "      break\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "      index +=1\n",
    "\n",
    "  plain_text += chr(index + ord('a'))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Plain Text :\",plain_text)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "### PlayFair Cipher"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "CjBJbSe_3AfR"
   },
   "source": [
    "- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-KjFbTK1IIw"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 116,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_table(key_text):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if len(key_text) > 25:\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if len(set(key_text)) != len(key_text):\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if 'j' in key_text:\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    key_table = [[None for _ in range(5)] for _ in range(5)]\n",
    "    # or\n",
    "    # key_table = [[None,None,None,None,None],\n",
    "    #              [None,None,None,None,None],\n",
    "    #              [None,None,None,None,None],\n",
    "    #              [None,None,None,None,None],\n",
    "    #              [None,None,None,None,None]]\n",
    "                 \n",
    "    key_list  = []\n",
    "    for char in key_text:\n",
    "        key_list.append(char)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    for char in \"abcdefghiklmnopqrstuvwxyz\":\n",
    "        if len(key_list) == 25:\n",
    "            break\n",
    "            \n",
    "        if char not in key_text:\n",
    "            key_list.append(char)\n",
    "            \n",
    "    for i in range(25):\n",
    "        col = i%5\n",
    "        row = (int) (i/5)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        key_table[row][col] = key_list[i]\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return key_table"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 151,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_bigrams(text):\n",
    "    bigrams = []\n",
    "    while (len(text)>0):\n",
    "        bigrams.append(text[:2])\n",
    "        text = text[2:]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    new_bigrams = []\n",
    "    for gram in bigrams:\n",
    "        if len(gram) != 2:\n",
    "            gram += 'x'\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if gram[0] == gram[1]:\n",
    "            gram = gram[0] + 'x'\n",
    "        \n",
    "        new_bigrams.append(gram)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return new_bigrams"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 159,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_coords(key_table,gram):\n",
    "    x1 = x2 = y1 = y2 = 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(5):\n",
    "        for j in range(5):\n",
    "            if key_table[i][j] == gram[0]:\n",
    "                x1 = j\n",
    "                y1 = i\n",
    "            if key_table[i][j] == gram[1]:\n",
    "                x2 = j\n",
    "                y2 = i\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return x1,y1,x2,y2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 215,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def encode(key_table,bigrams):\n",
    "    cipher_text = \"\"\n",
    "    for gram in bigrams:\n",
    "        x1,y1,x2,y2 = get_coords(key_table,gram)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if x1 == x2:\n",
    "            x1 = (x1 + 1)%5\n",
    "            x2 = (x2 + 1)%5\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if y1 == y2:\n",
    "            y1 = (y1 + 1)%5\n",
    "            y2 = (y2 + 1)%5\n",
    "        \n",
    "        cipher_text += key_table[x1][y1] + key_table[x2][y2] + \" \"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return cipher_text\n",
    "\n",
    "def decode(key_table,cipher_text):\n",
    "    plain_text  = \"\"\n",
    "    cipher_text = cipher_text.strip()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for gram in cipher_text.split(\" \"):\n",
    "        x1,y1,x2,y2 = get_coords(key_table,gram)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if x1 == x2:\n",
    "            x1 = (x1 - 1)%5\n",
    "            x2 = (x2 - 1)%5\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if y1 == y2:\n",
    "            y1 = (y1 - 1)%5\n",
    "            y2 = (y2 - 1)%5\n",
    "        \n",
    "        plain_text += key_table[x1][y1] + key_table[x2][y2]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return plain_text"
   ]
  },

    "\n",
    "plain_txt  = decode(key_table,cipher_txt)\n",
    "print(\"Plain Text  :\",plain_txt)"

   "source": [
    "### Hill Cipher"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "- https://youtu.be/mNGj_skw7Ck?si=7yYt4vZTZZshDdR3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 282,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sympy import Matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 279,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_keymatrix(key_text):\n",
    "    key_matrix = [[0,0],\n",
    "                  [0,0]]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if len(key_text) != 4:\n",
    "        print(\"Error: Require key of size 4\")\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for index , char in enumerate(key_text):\n",
    "        row = (int) (index / 2)\n",
    "        col = index % 2\n",
    "        \n",
    "        key_matrix[row][col] = ord(char) - ord('a')\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return key_matrix\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 278,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_bigrams(text):\n",
    "    bigrams = []\n",
    "    while (len(text) > 0):\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # IF UNABLE TO GET 2 CHARACTERS, ADD ONE EXTRA\n",
    "        gram_text = text[:2]\n",
    "        if len(gram_text) < 2:\n",
    "            gram_text = gram_text + \"x\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        bigrams.append(gram_text)\n",
    "        text = text[2:]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return bigrams"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 294,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def encrypt(bigrams,key_matrix):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    key_matrix  = np.array(key_matrix)\n",
    "    cipher_text = \"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for gram in bigrams:\n",
    "        gram_matrix  = np.array([ord(gram[0]) - ord('a'),\n",
    "                                 ord(gram[1]) - ord('a')])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        cipher_matrix = np.dot(key_matrix,gram_matrix) % 26\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for x in cipher_matrix:\n",
    "            cipher_text += chr(x + ord('a'))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        cipher_text += \" \"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return cipher_text\n",
    "\n",
    "def decrypt(cipher_text,key_matrix):\n",
    "    plain_text  = \"\"\n",
    "    key_matrix  = np.array(key_matrix)\n",
    "    cipher_text = cipher_text.strip()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Modular matrix Inverse of K matrix\n",
    "    inv_key_mat = Matrix(key_matrix).inv_mod(26)\n",
    "    inv_key_mat = np.array(inv_key_mat)\n",
    "\n",
    "    for gram in cipher_text.split(\" \"):\n",
    "        gram_matrix  = np.array([ord(gram[0]) - ord('a'),\n",
    "                                 ord(gram[1]) - ord('a')])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        plain_matrix = np.dot(inv_key_mat,gram_matrix) % 26\n",
    "        for x in plain_matrix:\n",
    "            plain_text += chr(x + ord('a'))\n",
    "            \n",
    "    return plain_text\n",
    "        "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 295,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []

   "outputs": [

      "Plain Text  : hellomydeardonkeyandmonkeysx\n"
     ]

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Hill cipher method using bigrams (2 characters).\n",
    "# This means a key matrix of 2x2 is required\n",
    "\n",
    "# input_text = input(\"Enter Plain Text : \")\n",
    "# key_text   = input(\"Enter Key   Text : \")\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = \"hello my dear donkey and monkeys\"\n",
    "key_text   = \"bblw\"\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = ''.join(input_text.split(' '))\n",
    "input_text = input_text.lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Generated Key Matrix\")\n",
    "key_matrix = generate_keymatrix(key_text)\n",
    "for row in key_matrix: \n",
    "    print(row)\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Generated Bigrams\")\n",
    "bigrams    = generate_bigrams(input_text)\n",
    "print(bigrams)\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "cipher_txt = encrypt(bigrams,key_matrix)\n",
    "print(\"Cipher Text :\",cipher_txt)\n",
    "\n",
    "plain_txt  = decrypt(cipher_txt,key_matrix)\n",
    "print(\"Plain Text  :\",plain_txt)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "### Polyalphabetic Cipher - Vignere\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- https://youtu.be/Ic4BzVggNY8?si=U7tbRuseF3T8snAT"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 308,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Cipher Text : ifwhpnjzfbczpovazbyznpygfzd\n",
      "Plain Text  : hellomydeardonkeyandmonkeys\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "input_text = \"hello my dear donkey and monkeys\"\n",
    "key_text   = \"bblw\"\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = ''.join(input_text.split(' '))\n",
    "input_text = input_text.lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Expand keys till length of plaintext\n",
    "expanded_key = \"\"\n",
    "while len(expanded_key) <= len(input_text):\n",
    "    expanded_key += key_text\n",
    "    \n",
    "expanded_key = expanded_key[:len(input_text)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encrypt\n",
    "cipher_text  = \"\"\n",
    "for key,char in zip(expanded_key,input_text):\n",
    "    key  = ord(key)  - ord('a')\n",
    "    char = ord(char) - ord('a')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ct   = (char+key) % 26\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cipher_text += chr(ct + ord('a'))\n",
    "    \n",
    "# Decrypt\n",
    "plain_text  = \"\"\n",
    "for key,char in zip(expanded_key,cipher_text):\n",
    "    key  = ord(key)  - ord('a')\n",
    "    char = ord(char) - ord('a')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    pt   = (char-key) % 26\n",
    "\n",
    "    plain_text += chr(pt + ord('a'))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "####\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Cipher Text :\",cipher_text)\n",
    "print(\"Plain Text  :\",plain_text)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "jp-MarkdownHeadingCollapsed": true,
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Polyalphabetic Cipher - Vernam"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- https://youtu.be/Qojvtgf7SQw?si=A1U4bBkiuAQrmpLV"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Cipher Text : gfa~pntvfb{vpmbszbgvnpg}fzz\n",
      "Plain Text  : hellomydeardonkeyandmonkeys\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "input_text = \"hello my dear donkey and monkeys\"\n",
    "key_text   = \"bblw\"\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = ''.join(input_text.split(' '))\n",
    "input_text = input_text.lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Expand keys till length of plaintext\n",
    "expanded_key = \"\"\n",
    "while len(expanded_key) <= len(input_text):\n",
    "    expanded_key += key_text\n",
    "    \n",
    "expanded_key = expanded_key[:len(input_text)]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encrypt\n",
    "cipher_text  = \"\"\n",
    "for key,char in zip(expanded_key,input_text):\n",
    "    key  = ord(key)  - ord('a')\n",
    "    char = ord(char) - ord('a')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ct   = (char^key)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cipher_text += chr(ct + ord('a'))\n",
    "    \n",
    "# Decrypt\n",
    "plain_text  = \"\"\n",
    "for key,char in zip(expanded_key,cipher_text):\n",
    "    key  = ord(key)  - ord('a')\n",
    "    char = ord(char) - ord('a')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    pt   = (char^key) \n",
    "\n",
    "    plain_text += chr(pt + ord('a'))\n",
    "    \n",
    "####\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Cipher Text :\",cipher_text)\n",
    "print(\"Plain Text  :\",plain_text)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "jp-MarkdownHeadingCollapsed": true,
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Rail Fence Technique"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- https://youtu.be/knE4G8DGLoY?si=X9A_hEZj1Woch01H"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Cipher Text : hlyaoenoe eodrnydny lmedkamks\n",
      "Plain Text  : hellomydeardonkeyandmonkeysey\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "input_text = \"hello my dear donkey and monkeys\"\n",
    "depth      = 3\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = ''.join(input_text.split(' '))\n",
    "input_text = input_text.lower() \n",
    "\n",
    "# Creating rails\n",
    "rails = [ \"\" for _ in range(depth) ]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encryption\n",
    "for index,char in enumerate(input_text):\n",
    "    selected_rail = index % depth\n",
    "    \n",
    "    rails[selected_rail] += char\n",
    "\n",
    "cipher_text = \" \".join(rails)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Decryption\n",
    "plain_text = \"\"\n",
    "rails      = cipher_text.split(\" \")\n",
    "for index,char in enumerate(cipher_text):\n",
    "    selected_rail_index = index % depth\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plain_text += rails [selected_rail_index][0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if len(rails[selected_rail_index]) > 1:\n",
    "        rails [selected_rail_index] = rails [selected_rail_index][1:]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Cipher Text :\",cipher_text)\n",
    "print(\"Plain Text  :\",plain_text)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "jp-MarkdownHeadingCollapsed": true,
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Columnar Cipher"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cPQXaYUMOjQ\n",
    "- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1cksV-Qf3jk"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 81,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Generated Rectangle:\n",
      "['h', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o', 'm', 'y']\n",
      "['d', 'e', 'a', 'r', 'd', 'o', 'n']\n",
      "['k', 'e', 'y', 'a', 'n', 'd', 'm']\n",
      "['o', 'n', 'k', 'e', 'y', 's', 'z']\n",
      "['z', 'z', 'z', 'z', 'z', 'z', 'z']\n",
      "\n",
      "Cipher Text : odnyz lraez eeenz laykz modsz ynmzz hdkoz \n",
      "Plain Text  : hellomydeardonkeyandmonkeyszzzzzzzz\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "input_text = \"hello my dear donkey and monkeys\"\n",
    "nrows      = 5\n",
    "ncols      = 7\n",
    "key        = \"4312560\"\n",
    "\n",
    "input_text = ''.join(input_text.split(' '))\n",
    "input_text = input_text.lower() \n",
    "\n",
    "#Expand input_text:\n",
    "while len(input_text) < (nrows*ncols):\n",
    "    input_text += \"z\"\n",
    "\n",
    "#Generate Rectangle\n",
    "rectangle  = [ [ \"\" for _ in range(ncols) ] for _ in range(nrows) ]\n",
    "\n",
    "for index, char in enumerate(input_text):\n",
    "    row = (int) (index / ncols)\n",
    "    col = index % ncols\n",
    "    \n",
    "    rectangle [row][col] = char\n",
    "    \n",
    "print(\"Generated Rectangle:\")\n",
    "for row in rectangle:\n",
    "    print(row)\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encryption\n",
    "cipher_text = \"\"\n",
    "for col in key:\n",
    "    col  = int(col)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for row in range(nrows):    \n",
    "        cipher_text += rectangle[row][col]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cipher_text += \" \"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "# Decryption       \n",
    "rectangle  = [ [ \"\" for _ in range(ncols) ] for _ in range(nrows) ]\n",
    "plain_text = \"\"\n",
    "cipher_txt = cipher_text.split(\" \")\n",
    "\n",
    "for index,col in enumerate(key):\n",
    "    col  = int(col)\n",
    "    for row in range(nrows):  \n",
    "        rectangle[row][col] = cipher_txt[index][row]    \n",
    "        \n",
    "for row in rectangle:\n",
    "    plain_text += \"\".join(row)\n",
    "\n",
    "####################\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Cipher Text :\",cipher_text)\n",
    "print(\"Plain Text  :\",plain_text)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### S - DES"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "- 8 bit PT\n",
    "- 10 bit Key"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 54,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def perm_k1(key):\n",
    "    return key[3]+key[1]+key[6]+key[0]+key[2]+key[7]+key[4]+key[8]+key[9]+key[5]\n",
    "\n",
    "def perm_k2(key):\n",
    "    return key[2]+key[1]+key[5]+key[4]+key[9]+key[6]+key[0]+key[7]\n",
    "\n",
    "def expanded_perm(str):\n",
    "    return str[3]+str[1]+str[2]+str[2]+str[1]+str[0]+str[0]+str[3]\n",
    "\n",
    "def ip(message):\n",
    "    return message\n",
    "\n",
    "def inv_ip(message):\n",
    "    return message"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 59,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def split(text):\n",
    "    return text[:len(text)//2],text[len(text)//2:]\n",
    "\n",
    "def xor(a,b):\n",
    "    s = ''\n",
    "    for i in range(len(a)):\n",
    "        s += str(int(a[i]) ^ int(b[i]))\n",
    "    return s"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 56,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def genkeys(key):\n",
    "    key   = perm_k1(key)\n",
    "    lh,rh = split(key)\n",
    "    lh    = \"\".join([text for text in lh[1:]]) + lh[0]\n",
    "    rh    = \"\".join([text for text in rh[1:]]) + rh[0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    k1 = key = perm_k2(lh + rh)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    lh,rh = split(key)\n",
    "    lh    = \"\".join([text for text in lh[1:]]) + lh[0]\n",
    "    rh    = \"\".join([text for text in rh[1:]]) + rh[0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    k2 = key = perm_k2(lh + rh)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return k1 , k2\n",
    "\n",
    "#genkeys('1010101010')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def sbox(data):\n",
    "    # 4 bit to 2 bit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 57,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def F(message,key):\n",
    "    message = expanded_perm(message)\n",
    "    km_xor  = xor(message,key)\n",
    "    return sbox(km_xor)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 58,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def encrypt(message,key):\n",
    "    k1 , k2 = genkeys(key)\n",
    "    message = ip(message)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    lh , rh = split(message)\n",
    "    f_res   = F(rh,k1)     \n",
    "    \n",
    "    cipher1 = rh + xor(f_res,lh)\n",
    "    lh , rh = split(cipher1)\n",
    "    f_res   = F(rh,k1)     \n",
    "    \n",
    "    cipher2 = rh + xor(f_res,lh)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return inv_ip(cipher2)    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "message = \"10111010\"\n",
    "key     = \"1010101010\"\n",
    "\n",
    "cipher  = encrypt(message,key)\n",
    "message = decrypt(cipher ,key)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### RSA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {
    "3b1f34c8-5854-49e5-92ab-09cd6dd9748d.png": {
     "image/png": ""
    },
    "434bda1f-d454-4b0f-9703-ff86eee0724c.png": {
     "image/png": ""
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![image.png](attachment:3b1f34c8-5854-49e5-92ab-09cd6dd9748d.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "![image.png](attachment:434bda1f-d454-4b0f-9703-ff86eee0724c.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 68,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(3, 7)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 68,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import math\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_e(n):\n",
    "  for i in range(2,n):\n",
    "        if math.gcd(i, n) == 1:\n",
    "          return i\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_d(e, p):\n",
    "  d_values = []\n",
    "  for d in range(1, p*2):\n",
    "        if (e * d) % p == 1:\n",
    "            d_values.append(d)\n",
    "  return d_values\n",
    "\n",
    "p = 3\n",
    "q = 11\n",
    "\n",
    "n = p*q\n",
    "phi_n = (p-1)*(q-1)\n",
    "e = get_e(phi_n)\n",
    "d = pow(e,-1,phi_n)  #get_d(e, phi_n)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "e,d"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 62,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Message data =  9\n",
      "Encrypted data =  3\n",
      "Original Message Sent =  9\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "msg = 9\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Message data = \", msg)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encryption c = (msg ^ e) % n\n",
    "c = msg**e%n\n",
    "print(\"Encrypted data = \", c)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Decryption m = (c ^ d) % n\n",
    "m = c**d%n\n",
    "print(\"Original Message Sent = \", m)"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {

   "source": [
    "### DSA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {
    "3f9b899c-e4d7-4005-861c-47944ae68dca.png": {
     "image/png": ""
    },
    "ffb19597-2302-494a-b5ed-2b3139bc0997.png": {

    }

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

    "\n",
    "![image.png](attachment:3f9b899c-e4d7-4005-861c-47944ae68dca.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {
    "38d35803-b78a-4b0e-b894-90fa0b892a84.png": {
     "image/png": ""
    },
    "54774161-3822-499b-bd50-d86b137f525c.png": {
     "image/png": ""
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![image.png](attachment:54774161-3822-499b-bd50-d86b137f525c.png)\n",
    "![image.png](attachment:38d35803-b78a-4b0e-b894-90fa0b892a84.png)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 72,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Signature verified\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "p = 797\n",
    "q = 199\n",
    "g = 81\n",
    "x = 17\n",
    "H_M = 123\n",
    "k = 30\n",
    "\n",
    "def gety(g, x, p):\n",
    "  return g**x%p\n",
    "\n",
    "def getinv(a, b):\n",
    "    for i in range(1, b+1):\n",
    "        if(i*a % b) == 1:\n",
    "            return i\n",
    "\n",
    "def getr(g, k, p, q):\n",
    "  return (g**k%p)%q\n",
    "\n",
    "def gets(k, h, x, r, q):\n",
    "  kinv = getinv(k, q)\n",
    "  return (kinv * (h + x*r))%q\n",
    "\n",
    "r = getr(g, k, p, q)\n",
    "s = gets(k, H_M, x, r, q)\n",
    "\n",
    "def getw(s, q):\n",
    "  sinv = getinv(s, q)\n",
    "  return sinv%q\n",
    "\n",
    "def getv(s, r, p, q, g, y, h):\n",
    "  w = getw(s, q)\n",
    "  u1 = h*w%q\n",
    "  u2 = r*w%q\n",
    "  return ((g**u1*y**u2)%p)%q\n",
    "\n",
    "y = gety(g, x, p)\n",
    "v = getv(s, r, p, q, g, y, H_M)\n",
    "\n",
    "if v==r:\n",
    "    print(\"Signature verified\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Signature not matching\")"
   ]
  },
